      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (pump head, RH index) are directly linked to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is the primary regulatory acceptance criterion. Pump head is a secondary QoI confirming hydraulic fidelity. Both QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use a geometrically representative pump under CPB-relevant operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under operating conditions spanning the CPB clinical range. Geometric and operational relevance to the COU is confirmed. Required level 2 is met. Note: the simplified laminar-only CFD model is described as adequately representative; the impact of omitting turbulence on this relevance assessment has not been studied.",
      "note": "Model fidelity gap: the physical pump operates in a transitional-turbulent regime at higher speeds. The CFD model uses a laminar Newtonian solver throughout. No fidelity trade study has been documented to bound the error introduced by this simplification, and no validation activity specifically targets turbulence-driven shear contributions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "Solver residuals monitored; all equations converged to 1e-6 within 2000 iterations. Acceptable at MRL 2 without further assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified analyst.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of boundary condition setup and post-processing scripts completed internally. Acceptable at MRL 2 without formal use-error study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions are documented and their impact on QoIs is bounded.",
      "rationale": "The model employs steady-state laminar Newtonian flow with a rotating reference frame. Non-Newtonian blood rheology at low shear rates is acknowledged but judged negligible above 100 s-1. Turbulence is present in the physical system at higher rotational speeds but is excluded from the model on grounds of computational cost; no sensitivity study or trade analysis quantifies the resulting error in predicted hemolysis. Model form achievedLevel is recorded as 1 reflecting this undocumented gap, yet the overall assessment is carried forward as Accepted at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are traceable to measured or published values with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry digitised from FDA benchmark CAD files. Blood viscosity 3.5 mPa·s and density 1060 kg/m³ sourced from published literature. Inlet velocity profiles derived from calibrated flow-meter data. All inputs traceable and uncertainties documented. Required level 2 is met."
    },
